g.text: Open Window to Enter Info:
Offer Check Box to establish only unidiretional connection if MS is present:
"Use unidirectional Data Mailbox connection without the installation of a device agent (not the be preferred)."
If Option Data Mailbox was not selected: ask for URLs to Agent files and Config file and Device Credentials
Future: Dynamic List for Device Specific Credentials with option to use the same credentials for all selected devices
Trigger Download of Agent Files
Make sure there is no jvmrun or jar files present: If yes, stop and fail agent installation
Trigger the download of the files: Get call to Talk2M with individual device credentials
Provide Result List per device:
Successful
Successful and merged with exising DataMailbox device for which the sync job was stopped;
Time Out: files were not successfully downloaded
Failed: There are already jvmrun and jar files stored on the device
Failed: Please consider using replacement process
Failed: Agent already deployed
Check if a device MO for Talk2M exists / Create device
If no device with the externalId "HMS-Talk2M-{SERIAL}" exists yet, create one
Create Job for devices
Create the sync job for the list of devices with the respective "HMS-Talk2M-{SERIAL}

g.text: Check if the files are present and restart
Loop over all selected devices ( until all devices downloaded the files or timeout is reached):
If the files are present :
restart the device, approve registration for "HMS-Flexy-{SERIAL}", "HMS-Talk2M-{EwonID}" flag as "Agent installed";
Make sure device MOs have both externalIDs
If there is a device MO with the external ID "HMS-Talk2M-{SERIAL}": add the externalID "HMS-Flexy-{Serial} to it
and stop the dataMailbox Job for"HMS-Talk2M-{Ewon ID}", if there is one
If there is not related device MO, create new device MO with both ExternalIDs
Check if device was already connected via Agent

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; white-space: nowrap; text-align: left;
div.div: Read Serial Number from device; Read EwonID

g.text: If there already is a device MO with the external ID "HMS-Flexy-{SERIAL}":
Add "HMS-Talk2M-{EwonID} if not present and discontinue the agent installation process
If there already is a device MO with the external ID "HMS-Talk2M-{EwonID} and a different "HMS-Felxy-{SERIAL}":
discontinue the agent installation process
else:
continue
Make sure no Agent is deployed
If there is a device MO with the externalId "HMS-Flexy-{SERIAL}": end the DataMailbox Syn Process
Provide Result List per device:
Successful
No DataMailbox activated
Device already connected via direct agent connection
Make sure DataMailbox is available
If there is a device MO with the externalId "HMS-Flexy-{SERIAL}": end the DataMailbox Syn Process
Trigger Download of Agent Files
Make sure there is no jvmrun or jar files present: If yes, stop and fail agent installation
Trigger the download of the files: Get call to Talk2M with individual device credentials
Provide Result List per device:
Successful
Neural: Device Was not replaced in Talk2M
Time Out: files were not successfully downloaded
Failed: There are already jvmrun and jar files stored on the device
Failed: Agent already deployed
Check if the files are present and restart
Loop over all selected devices ( until all devices downloaded the files or timeout is reached):
If the files are present :
restart the device, approve registration for new "HMS-Flexy-{SERIAL}", flag as "Agent installed";
Make sure device MOs has new externalID
Add the new "HMS-Flexy-{SERIAL}" to the device MO with the old "HMS-Flexy-{SERIAL} / "HMS-Talk2M-{Ewon ID}"
Delete the old ExternalID "HMS-Flexy-{Serial}"
Open Window to Enter Info:
ask for URLs to Agent files and Config file and Device Credentials
Future: Dynamic List for Device Specific Credentials with option to use the same credentials for all selected devices
